<subSubSection id="C33A651A98345A36DADCFD58D1A0FC62" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9F369198345A36DADCFD58D1A0FC62" blockId="40.[189,1399,721,899]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<taxonomicName id="4C204D1298345A36DADCFD58D3C0FD0D" authorityName="J. Eric Hill" authorityYear="1942" box="[189,469,723,749]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ruwenzorii">
<emphasis id="B954EA8398345A36DADCFD58D3C0FD0D" box="[189,469,723,749]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Rhinolophus ruwenzorii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a very restricted distribution of approximately 
<quantity id="4CD89B7498345A36DE7AFD58D664FD0D" box="[1051,1137,723,749]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" unit="km" value="360.0">360 km</quantity>
<quantity id="4CD89B7498345A36DE10FD5AD683FD0D" box="[1137,1174,721,749]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" unit="in" value="2.0">
<superScript id="7C559BD998345A36DE10FD5AD66FFD3F" attach="left" box="[1137,1146,721,735]" fontSize="6" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">2</superScript>
in
</quantity>
the 
<collectingCountry id="F337760198345A36DEA2FD58D6EAFD0D" box="[1219,1279,723,749]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">DRC</collectingCountry>
provinces of Nord-Kivu and Ituri (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B6098345A36DBB5FD73D08CFCF2" author="Fahr" box="[468,665,760,786]" firstAuthor="Fahr" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" pagination="342 - 343" refId="ref260180" refString="Fahr J. 2013 c. Rhinolophus maclaudi Maclaud's Horseshoe Bat. In: Happold M. &amp; Happold D. (eds) Mammals of Africa Volume IV. Hedgehogs, Shrews and Bats: 342 - 343. Bloomsbury Publishing, London." type="book chapter" year="2013" yearSuffix="c">Fahr 2013c: 342</bibRefCitation>
). Some authors (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B6098345A36D9F3FD73D66AFCF2" author="Smith &amp; Hood" box="[914,1151,760,786]" firstAuthor="Smith" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" pagination="163 - 171" refId="ref273285" refString="Smith J. D. &amp; Hood C. S. 1980. Additional material of Rhinolophus ruwenzorii Hill, 1942, with comments on its natural history and taxonomic status. In: Wilson D. E. &amp; Gardner A. L. (eds) Proceedings of the Fifth International Bat Research Conference: 163 - 171. Texas Press, Lubbock, Texas." type="book chapter" year="1980">Smith &amp; Hood 1980</bibRefCitation>
) consider 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D1298345A36DE96FD72D763FCF2" authorityName="J. Eric Hill" authorityYear="1942" box="[1271,1398,761,786]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ruwenzorii">
<emphasis id="B954EA8398345A36DE96FD72D763FCF2" box="[1271,1398,761,786]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">ruwenzorii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be a subspecies of the west African 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D1298345A36D8CAFC95D12BFCD8" authorityName="Pousargues" authorityYear="1897" box="[683,830,798,824]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="maclaudi">
<emphasis id="B954EA8398345A36D8CAFC95D12BFCD8" box="[683,830,798,824]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">R. maclaudi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which would result in an extremely disjunct distribution for this species (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B6098345A36D870FCC8D0E7FCBD" author="Baeten" box="[529,754,835,861]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Baeten" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" pagination="183 - 196" refId="ref256654" refString="Baeten B., Van Cakenberghe V. &amp; De Vree F. 1984. An annotated inventory of a collection of bats from Rwanda (Chiroptera). Revue de zoologie africaine 98 (1): 183 - 196." type="journal article" year="1984">
Baeten 
<emphasis id="B954EA8398345A36D80FFCCFD0BFFCBD" box="[622,682,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">et al.</emphasis>
1984
</bibRefCitation>
). However, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B6098345A36D9E3FCC8D641FCBD" author="Fahr" box="[898,1108,835,861]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Fahr" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" pagination="95 - 126" refId="ref261109" refString="Fahr J., Vierhaus H., Hutterer R. &amp; Kock D. 2002. A revision of the Rhinolophus maclaudi species group with the description of a new species from West Africa (Chiroptera: Rhinolophidae). Myotis 40: 95 - 126." type="journal article" year="2002">
Fahr 
<emphasis id="B954EA8398345A36D9A0FCCFD1E8FCBD" box="[961,1021,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">et al.</emphasis>
(2002)
</bibRefCitation>
showed that both forms differ substantially and should be considered as separate species.
</paragraph>
